The paper deals with a communication system using one-bit ADCs, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The paper also proposes a novel MIMO detection framework, which involves coding theory concepts such as channel coding and minimum distance decoding, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (signal processing), cs.NI (networking), and cs.SY (systems and control).
